org.sql: SELECT projects.* FROM projects INNER JOIN members ON projects.id = members.project_id LEFT OUTER JOIN projects AS projects_members ON projects_members.id = members.project_id LEFT OUTER JOIN member_roles ON member_roles.member_id = members.id LEFT OUTER JOIN roles ON roles.id = member_roles.role_id WHERE members.user_id = "$1" AND (projects.active = True OR project_id IS NULL) AND projects.active = "$2" ORDER BY projects.name ASC
